aiAnalysis.summary: This is Australia's 2025 Implementation Plan for the Data and Digital Government Strategy, with Artificial Intelligence as one of four key priorities. It outlines how the Australian government plans to capture AI opportunities for productivity gains and improved digital service delivery as part of their 2030 vision for government services.
agencies: Department of Finance - Data and Digital

aiAnalysis.summary: The Australian Government's Data and Digital Government Strategy sets out a 2030 vision for digital transformation of public services. While not AI-specific, it establishes the strategic framework that would govern AI implementation in government services and mentions an AI transparency statement.

The Data and Digital Government Strategy by the Digital Transformation Agency sets out Australia's 2030 vision for digital transformation of public services, including an AI transparency statement. While not specifically focused on AI policy, it provides the foundational framework for government digital capabilities that would encompass AI governance.
General overview page of DTA initiatives focusing on digital transformation, procurement, and government architecture - no specific AI policy content

title: Harnessing tech to drive faster decisions across Defence | Defence

aiAnalysis.summary: Australian Government investing $40 million in AI and emerging technologies for Defence through ASCA's EDT program, focusing on Decision Advantage capabilities including machine reasoning, automated data integration, and AI across defence domains.
